title: Cron jobs deliver response text instead of prompt text
---
User clarified intended semantics: after a cron job fires, clawq should send the cron prompt/message to the channel, not wait for the LLM turn and deliver the LLM response text. Current scheduler behavior in src/scheduler.ml calls Session.turn with job.message and then delivers result via deliver_fn ~text:result. This produced visible CRON_ACK when user expected the cron prompt itself. Acceptance criteria:
- Scheduler/channel delivery semantics for cron are aligned with intended product behavior
- Cron sends the configured prompt/message to the channel rather than the model response
- Logs and run history reflect the correct delivered payload semantics
- Tests cover the intended cron delivery behavior